Integration

Integrating FishHook into scripts is simple. Just place this line of code where you wish a plugin hook to be available.

($hook = FishHook::hook('some_hook')) ? eval($hook) : false;

Just change the hook name "some_hook" to a more detailed name.

---------------------------

Database table

CREATE TABLE `plugin_code` (
  `id` bigint(20) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `title` varchar(255) COLLATE utf8_unicode_ci NOT NULL,
  `hook` mediumtext COLLATE utf8_unicode_ci NOT NULL,
  `code` longtext COLLATE utf8_unicode_ci NOT NULL,
  `execorder` bigint(20) NOT NULL,
  `enabled` smallint(6) NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB  DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8 COLLATE=utf8_unicode_ci;

---------------------------

Example plugin

INSERT INTO `plugin_code` (`id`, `title`, `hook`, `code`, `execorder`, `enabled`) VALUES
(1, 'My Plugin', 'some_hook', 'echo "my plugin code";', 0, 1);